title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 §§ 23-10.7 - Environmental requirements
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 §§ 23-10.7 - Environmental requirements

State Regulations

Exhaust gases from internal combustion engines shall be
discharged into the atmosphere in accordance with the rules and regulations of
appropriate jurisdictional authorities concerned with environmental
conditions. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12
§§
23-10.7

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
